In a microservices architecture, the API Gateway Service is the single entry
point for all client requests. It routes requests to appropriate services, handles
authentication, rate limiting, load balancing, and may provide logging and
response transformation.
You're using Spring Cloud Gateway, so hereâ€™s a full guide including API
structure, use cases, and configurations for the API Gateway Service.
âœ… API Gateway Service â€“ Spring Cloud Gateway
ğŸ“ Base URL: Client-facing â†’ https://api.myecommerce.com/**
ğŸ“ Internally proxies to microservices like /product/** , /order/** , etc.
ğŸ”§ Main Responsibilities
Feature Handled by Gateway? Notes
Routing requests âœ… Based on path or host
Authentication & JWT parsing âœ… With filter
Rate limiting âœ… Redis-based or in-memory
Circuit breaking âœ… Resilience4j/Hystrix
Load balancing âœ… Eureka + Ribbon
CORS âœ… Global config
Centralized logging/tracing âœ… Sleuth / Zipkin
Request/response transformation âœ… Optional pre/post filters
ğŸš€ Sample Routes Configuration ( application.yml )
